A diagnosis&nbsp;of Fuhrmann syndrome can be made when a doctor observes signs and symptoms consistent with the syndrome.[13680] Diagnosis can be confirmed by&nbsp;<a href="https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/primer/testing/genetictesting">genetic testing</a>&nbsp;that finds two changes in the&nbsp;<em><a href="https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/gene/WNT7A">WNT7A</a>&nbsp;</em><em>&nbsp;</em><a href="https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/primer/basics/gene">gene</a>.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Another syndrome called&nbsp;<a href="https://rarediseases.info.nih.gov/diseases/9212/ulna-and-fibula-absence-of-with-severe-limb-deficiency">Al-Awadi-Raas-Rothschild syndrome</a>&nbsp;is also caused by mutations to the&nbsp;<em>WNT7A&nbsp;</em>gene.&nbsp;In some cases, the exact same genetic change can cause one syndrome in one person and the other syndrome in another person. Therefore, diagnosis of these syndromes should be made based on the clinical features of each individual person.[13682]&nbsp;
